The article lists several nominations that have been sent to the Senate. Some of the nominations include Alvin Brown for a position in the National Transportation Safety Board, David Crane for Under Secretary of Energy, Kathleen A. FitzGibbon as Ambassador to the Republic of Niger, and Eric W. Kneedler as Ambassador to the Republic of Rwanda. Other nominations include Alan J. Patricof for a position in the Securities Investor Protection Corporation, Elizabeth Rood as Ambassador to Turkmenistan, Bijan Sabet as Ambassador to the Czech Republic, and Juan Eduardo Sanchez as Federal Cochairperson of the Southwest Border Regional Commission. Additionally, Colleen Joy Shogan has been nominated to be the Archivist of the United States, Robert Harley Shriver III as Deputy Director of the Office of Personnel Management, Jay T. Snyder as a Member of the United States Advisory Commission on Public Diplomacy, and Richard L.A. Weiner as United States Director of the European Bank for Reconstruction and Development.